  "text": "The xDS v3 transport protocol implementation in Envoy is spread across multiple files in source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/. The architecture consists of two distinct implementation paths:\n\n1. **Legacy Implementations (Pre-Unified Mux):**\n   - GrpcMuxImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc): Implements State-of-the-World (SotW) xDS protocol, handling discovery requests/responses for resource discovery\n   - NewGrpcMuxImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc): Implements Delta xDS protocol, providing incremental updates for improved efficiency\n   - Both are complete implementations managing gRPC streams, multiplexing subscriptions, and handling protocol state\n\n2. **Unified Template-Based Implementation (Unified Mux):**\n   - The xds_mux subdirectory contains a modern template-based approach using GrpcMuxImpl as a template class (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h/.cc)\n   - GrpcMuxSotw and GrpcMuxDelta are template specializations of GrpcMuxImpl that instantiate it with:\n     - SotwSubscriptionState/SotwSubscriptionStateFactory for SotW mode\n     - DeltaSubscriptionState/DeltaSubscriptionStateFactory for Delta mode\n   - BaseSubscriptionState (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/subscription_state.h) provides the abstract parent for protocol state management\n   - SotwSubscriptionState (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/sotw_subscription_state.h/.cc) tracks SotW protocol state\n   - DeltaSubscriptionState (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/delta_subscription_state.h/.cc) tracks Delta protocol state\n\n3. **Adapter and Factory:**\n   - GrpcSubscriptionImpl (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h/.cc) is the adapter that bridges typed Subscription interface to the untyped GrpcMux interface\n   - GrpcConfigSubscriptionFactory (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_factory.h/.cc) selects between SotW and Delta modes based on runtime features and API configuration, instantiating either the legacy or unified mux implementations\n\n4. **Supporting Infrastructure:**\n   - WatchMap (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/watch_map.h/.cc) manages watches/subscriptions for individual resources, multiplexing multiple subscribers to the same resource\n   - GrpcMuxContext (source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_context.h) encapsulates parameters needed for mux creation\n\nThe implementation supports both legacy and unified mux modes, with a migration path from separate GrpcMuxImpl and NewGrpcMuxImpl to a unified template-based approach through GrpcMuxSotw and GrpcMuxDelta specializations."
